#: ../../C/Christmas-tree-packet.rst:5
msgid "Christmas tree packet"
msgstr "Christmas tree packet"

#: ../../C/Christmas-tree-packet.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/Christmas-tree-packet.rst:9
msgid ""
"A packet with every single option set for whatever protocol is in use. See "
":ref:`kamikaze-packet`\\, :ref:`Chernobyl-packet`\\. (The term doubtless "
"derives from a fanciful image of each little option bit being represented by"
" a different-colored light bulb, all turned on.) Compare "
":ref:`Godzillagram`\\."
msgstr ""
"使用中のプロトコルが何であれ、あらゆるオプションを一つ残らず立てたパケット。\\ :ref:`kamikaze-packet`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`Chernobyl-packet`\\ "
"を参照。(この用語は間違いなく、それぞれの小さなオプションビットが異なる色の電球で表され、それがすべて点灯しているという空想的なイメージに由来します。)"
" \\ :ref:`Godzillagram`\\ と比較せよ。"
